<Author>jjrpaul
<Content>Ok Hotel My wife and I stayed there for three nights. the location is excellent, just a block from the Duomo and a short walk to most everything else. For such a location, the price of 108 Euro was perfect. It's a15 min walk to the RR station, certainly do-able. Our room was adequate in size, overlooking the inner courtyard. We could never figure out the layout of the hotel, as the corridors wind all over. The hotel is located on the third floor, and when you first arrive at the street entrance and go in, you feel like you may have made a mistake picking the place, as it has no attractiveness at all, and a tiny elevator. But when you get off on the third floor, it gets much more homey. The front desk has a lived in living room charm to it, with sofas and older upholstered chairs, along with a computer for internet access. The room itself was adequate in size and clean, but the TV was mounted on the wall and watching it from the bed was a bit awkward. But we didn't come to Florence to watch TV anyway! The bathroom was the main thing we disliked about the whole experience. It was incredibly narrow, so much so that you could hardly get off the potty without carefully adjusting your limbs!! The shower stall was also small, with a shower head that was defective, so water went everywhere. Thank God there was a plastic shower curtain that was somewhat effective.There was also a mold problem in the bathroom, too.Breakfast was good, in a large room, with a good selection of cereals, juices, fruit salad, yogurt, breads, and croissants. Among the better ones we have had in Italy. All things considered, it was an ok experience. I would consider staying there again, but would look elsewhere first. The price was right, the location excellent, and the food good. But I am not sure that I would recommend the place to my best friends for fear that they would be distressed over the bathrooms. 
